 An alumnus of Boschrand Primary School, Ntombifuthi Sibanyoni, made Valentine’s Day worthwhile for
26 needy learners from the school. Accompanied by members of the ANC Women’s League and local councillor, Kenneth Mkhonto, Sibanyoni donated new school uniforms for boys and girls, as well as sanitary packs with cosmetics for the first 26 names on the list of 52 needy children. “I started the project a long time ago as a way of giving back to the community I grew up in. ALSO READ:Raising financially responsible children This year we had to up the levels and give to more children. The packages were made up according to each child’s needs, as indicated on the list I received from the school,”she said..  